00028 // USABILITY: The abundant use of dynamic_cast makes it seem like something's wrong with the whole dataflow design.  And I
00029 //            couldn't find any documentation about when it's okay to cast from Lattice to one of its subclasses, so I've made
00030 //            the assumption throughout that when the dynamic_cast returns null, the node in question points to a variable or
00031 //            expression that the live/dead analysis has determined to be dead.
00032 //
00033 // USABILITY: No doxygen comments throughout genericDataflow framework?!?  But it looks like there's some doxygen-like stuff
00034 //            describing a few function parameters, so is it using some other documenting system?  I at least added the headers
00035 //            to the docs/Rose/rose.cfg file so doxygen picks up the structure.
00036 //
00037 // USABILITY: The genericDataflow framework always produces files named "index.html", "summary.html", and "detail.html" and
00038 //            a directory named "dbg_imgs" regardless of any debug settings.  These are apprently the result of the Dbg::init()
00039 //            call made from the main program, and this call is required (omitting it results in segmentation faults).  The
00040 //            file names are constant and therefore one should expect tests to clobber each other's outputs when run in
00041 //            parallel.  The contents of the files cannot be trusted.  Furthermore, since these are HTML files, an aborted test
00042 //            will generate only a partial HTML file which some browsers will choke on.

00054 class TaintLattice: public FiniteLattice {
00055 public:
00056 
00060     enum Vertex {
00061         VERTEX_BOTTOM,                  
00062         VERTEX_UNTAINTED,               
00063         VERTEX_TAINTED,                 
00064         // no need for a top since that would imply that the value is tainted. I.e., VERTEX_TAINTED *is* our top.
00065     };
00066 
00067 protected:
00068     Vertex vertex;                      
00070 public:
00071 
00073     TaintLattice(): vertex(VERTEX_BOTTOM) {}
00074 
00076     virtual void initialize() /*override*/ {
00077         *this = TaintLattice();
00078     }
00079 
00083     Vertex get_vertex() const { return vertex; }
00084     bool set_vertex(Vertex v);
00089     virtual Lattice *copy() const /*override*/ {
00090         return new TaintLattice(*this);
00091     }
00092 
00093     // USABILITY: The base class defines copy() without a const argument, so we must do the same here.
00096     virtual void copy(/*const*/ Lattice *other_) /*override*/;
00097 
00098 
00099     // USABILITY: The base class defines '==' with non-const argument and "this", so we must do the same here.
00100     // USABILITY: This is not a real equality predicate since it's not reflexive.  In other words, (A==B) does not imply (B==A)
00101     //            for all values of A and B.
00103     virtual bool operator==(/*const*/ Lattice *other_) /*const*/ /*override*/;
00104 
00105     // USABILITY: The base class defines str() with non-const "this", so we must do the same here.  That means that if we want
00106     //            to use this functionality from our own methods (that have const "this") we have to distill it out to some
00107     //            other place.
00108     // USABILITY: The "prefix" argument is pointless. Why not just use StringUtility::prefixLines() in the base class rather
00109     //            than replicate this functionality all over the place?
00113     virtual std::string str(/*const*/ std::string /*&*/prefix) /*const*/ /*override*/ {
00114         return prefix + to_string();
00115     }
00116 
00117     // USABILITY: We define this only because of deficiencies with the "str" signature in the base class.  Otherwise our
00118     //            printing method (operator<<) could just use str().  We're trying to avoid evil const_cast.
00121     std::string to_string() const;
00122 
00123     // USABILITY: The base class defines meetUpdate() with a non-const argument, so we must do the same here.
00125     virtual bool meetUpdate(/*const*/ Lattice *other_) /*override*/;
00126 
00127     friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream &o, const TaintLattice &lattice);
00128 };
